Khrushchev's call for summit meeting continues Soviet campaign to contain Western intervention.\n\nGeneral increase in Soviet military communications activity noted on 18-20 July.\n\nSoviet diplomats in Balkan capitals return to Moscow.\n\nEast German regime organizing demonstrations in connection with Adenauer's Berlin visit this week.\n\nII. ASIA-AFRICA\n\nLebanese Army commander still hoping to obtain withdrawal of US troops. Preparations continue for Syrian-supported revolt against Jordanian Government.\n\nFree World comment on US policies and Khrushchev's summit proposal.\n\nCambodia agrees to give diplomatic recognition to Communist China", "token_count": 91, "token_end_0based": 90, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "21 july 1958 i the communist bloc khrushchev's call for summit meeting continues soviet campaign to contain western intervention general increase in soviet military communications activity noted on 18-20 july soviet diplomats in balkan capitals return to moscow east german regime organizing demonstrations in connection with adenauer's berlin visit this week ii asia-africa lebanese army commander still hoping to obtain withdrawal of us troops preparations continue for syrian-supported revolt against jordanian government free world comment on us policies and khrushchev's summit proposal cambodia agrees to give diplomatic recognition to communist china", "unred_source_page": 3}
